                            <comment id="46272" author="luke" created="Sun, 23 Aug 2009 03:51:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1226&quot; title=&quot;Introduce RedirectStrategy to replace RedirectUtils&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1226&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1226&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will introduce a general strategy for redirects which should also be used here. Closing as duplicate. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46680" author="luke" created="Sun, 13 Sep 2009 08:00:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that there are configuration limitations on the use of the redirect strategy for the standard LoginUrlAuthenticationEntryPoint (formerly AuthenticationProcessingFilterEntryPoint). For example, if it is attempting to redirect to an HTTPS URL, and a context-relative redirect strategy is used, then you will lose the HTTPS part. If necessary the entry point code should be overridden or a custom strategy should be written to make sure you end up with URLs that make sense to your clients and which work the way you want.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
